# Figma ↔ RTL — placement rules

## 1. User language: “שמאל / ימין”

When the stakeholder says **left / right** (`שמאל` / `ימין`), treat it as **physical screen edges** unless they explicitly mean **inline-start / inline-end** in the reading direction.

- For **photo overlays**, **floating badges**, and **decorative numerals** that must stay on a specific side of the image **regardless of `dir`**, prefer **`left` / `right`** (and `top` / `bottom`) on the positioned element.
- **`inset-inline-start` / `inset-inline-end`** follow the **ancestor’s `dir`**. Under `dir="rtl"`, `inline-end` is the physical **left** — but it is easy to confuse with Figma’s **LTR `x` from left** and ship the wrong side. **Physical `left`/`right` avoids that class of bug.**

## 2. Figma Dev Mode `x`, `y`

- Figma frames are often authored in **LTR file space** (`x` grows to the right).
- To mirror to the live **RTL** page, either:
  - Document **both** “LTR-from-left” and **intended physical side** in the cache, or
  - Implement overlays with **explicit `left`/`right`** once the physical target is confirmed (e.g. badge on **physical left** of the hero column).

## 3. Repeated pattern: chapter number + red waves

Large **Salsa** chapter digits with **red wave strokes** on the numbers are implemented once in **`BigChapterDigits`** (`src/components/chapter2/mobile/BigChapterDigits.jsx`). Reuse it for new chapters instead of a separate “wave below the number” SVG unless Figma explicitly differs.

## 4. Decorative numerals remain LTR

Keep **`dir="ltr"`** on the numeric group when Figma uses **left-aligned** display numerals; the **position** of the group is still chosen with **physical** or **logical** coords per sections 1–2.
